kodkod.engine.satlab
Enum SATFactory

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<SATFactory>
      kodkod.engine.satlab.SATFactory
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SATFactory>
public enum SATFactory
extends java.lang.Enum<SATFactory>

An enumeration of available SAT solvers whose members are factories for SATSolver instances of a given type.

Author:
Emina Torlak

Enum Constant Summary
ActiveLearning
          The factory for instances of the sat4j "active learning" solver that uses First UIP clause generator, watched literals, etc.
Backjumping
          The factory for instances of the "backjumping" sat4j solver with VSIDS heuristics, FirstUIP clause generator for backjumping but no learning.
DefaultSAT4J
          The factory for instances of the default sat4j solver.
LightSAT4J
          The factory for instances of the "light" sat4j solver that is suitable for solving many small instances of SAT problems.
MiniLearning
          The factory for instances of the "minilearning" sat4j solver that learns clauses of size smaller than 10 % of the total number of variables
Relsat
          The factory for instances of the sat4j "relsat" solver with decision UIP clause generator.
ZChaff
          The factory for instances that provide access to the basic functionality of the zchaff solver from Princeton; the returned instances support only basic sat solver operations (adding variables/clauses, solving, and obtaining a satisfying solution, if any).
ZChaffPlus
          The factory for instances that proivde access to the core extraction functionality of the zchaff solver from Princeton; the SATSolver.isCoreExtractor() method of the returned instances returns true.

ZChaffPlus

public static final SATFactory ZChaffPlus
The factory for instances that proivde access to the core extraction functionality of the zchaff solver from Princeton; the SATSolver.isCoreExtractor() method of the returned instances returns true. Note that core extraction can incur a significant memory overhead during solving, so if you do not need this functionality, use the ZChaff factory instead.
